o An abstraction layer which Introduces two classes to manage user-defined data types, facilitating the
storage of diverse data attributes while maintaining a user-friendly interface.
o Dynamic Data Storage: Utilizes a templated BST structure to accommodate various data types,
ensuring flexibility and scalability in data management.
o Data Insertion, Search and Removal: Implements functions for inserting, searching and deleting
nodes, including support for unique data constraints and subtree removal.
o Data Persistence: Features capabilities for saving and loading data to and from files with indexed
storage, optimizing retrieval times through structured file management.
o Data Validation: Incorporates functions to validate sorted data inputs from various sources, ensuring
that the database maintains integrity during operations.
o Auto-Detection: Automatically detects if the dataset is sorted to generate the tree faster and maintain
its balance.
